Loyal Member of Giliath Lang</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukainite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kainite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/30/02 8:20:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I think we all agree...</span><hr size=1> I think we all agree that at least the resists are out of whack for the most part, due to twinkage. This makes it immposible for the casters to get effective spells off without being resisted (their are some notable exceptions, but mostly HIGH level, such as some magic based DoTs like splurt, Winged Death, and Lures and such). The problem is that Verant's solution, while a good idea in theory to me, of suggested levels (making them not work well below them also) is so out of whack, it's retarded. They have the level restrictions on some things so high they will never get used, cause you can get something equal or better from an easier and lower level mob to fight somewhere else. <br>
<br>
